{"title":"Bikerumor merges with GearJunkie, Switchback Travel & more!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/19/bikerumor-merges-with-gearjunkie-switchback-travel-more/","date":1613770832000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Bikerumor has joined Lola Digital Media, aligning with leading outdoor sites like GearJunkie, Switchback Travel, AutoWise, iRunFar, and others to create the AllGear Media Group. I’m very happy and proud to say that our entire team – Zach, Cory, Jessie-May, Steve, Jordan, Kristi, and the rest of the crew (including me) – are all still here.</p><h2>Wait, <em>what?!?</em></h2><figure id=\"attachment_251722\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251722\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" alt=\"riding mountain bikes in france\" width=\"945\" height=\"629\" sizes=\"(max-width: 945px) 100vw, 945px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x322/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 945w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-800x532.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-768x511.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-696x463.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-631x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 631w\" ezoid=\"0.3938008729658089\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 945w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-800x532.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-768x511.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-696x463.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/first-press-camp-for-bikerumor-631x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 631w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251722\">One of the first press launches I ever attended was for GT in France in 2010. Remember 26″ mountain bike wheels?</figcaption></figure><p>In late December 2020, Bikerumor was acquired by Lola Digital Media. The official press releases are <a href=\"https://www.loladigitalmedia.com/bikerumor-joins-lola-digital-media/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a> and <a href=\"https://www.loladigitalmedia.com/lola-digital-media-announces-allgear-group/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>. That’s the short version. But I wanted to tell you about the deal in my own words, so here’s the long version:</p><p>I started Bikerumor in 2008, mainly because I didn’t want to get a real job. I was closing down a beverage company I’d started almost a decade earlier that, for various reasons, had run its course. An office job wasn’t an option because, well, I’d just really rather be outside riding mountain bikes.</p><p>As a cyclist, I was most interested in making my bike lighter and faster. <em>Training?</em> Meh, I just needed a lighter bike! I loved the bikes, the gear, the components, and the tech.</p><p>I was also a big fan of Engadget, the tech blog. Its simple layout, endless scroll of new gadgets, and fun, lighthearted writing style really appealed to me. There was nothing like that in the cycling world.</p><p>Other sites did race coverage and forums really well. But I couldn’t find a daily stream of all the new bikes and tech. So I made the cycling tech blog I wanted to read, and called it Bikerumor.</p><h3>The timing was great.</h3><figure id=\"attachment_251720\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251720\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck.jpg\" alt=\"tyler standing in front of giant dump truck\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-265x198.jpg 265w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-tyler-in-front-of-dump-truck-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251720\">To pay for my trip to Interbike in 2008, I helped a friend with their booth at the Mine Show across town, then rushed straight back to the bike show…after checking out these insane industrial machines for a few minutes, of course!</figcaption></figure><p>The big magazines were committed to print because subscriptions and full-page display ads made them a lot of money. Digital would disrupt that, of course, but they reacted slowly. The other websites had found their niches covering the races and athletes.</p><p>The door was open to do something different, so I put a camera on my already nearly maxed out credit card and bought a plane ticket to Interbike.</p><p>I didn’t really know what to expect, but I had a plan: Walk around, ask every booth what they were launching at the show, and take some pictures and notes.</p><p>Then I went back to the hotel and cranked out stories until I passed out. Repeat for three days.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251719\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251719\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012.jpg\" alt=\"bikerumor team at interbike\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-265x198.jpg 265w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-crew-at-interbike-2012-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251719\">The crew at Interbike 2012’s CrossVegas…Marc, Colin, Watts, Nick, me, and Evan.</figcaption></figure><p>I did the same thing at Sea Otter Classic in April 2009. And NAHBS. And then Interbike again. Eventually, Zach joined my team. Then Cory. And all along, Kristi’s been behind the scenes moderating comments and posting your Pics of the Day.</p><p>I’m humbled that all of them have stayed with me for so long, many times keeping me in check, or offering up big new story ideas, and are an integral part of the Bikerumor family.</p><p>More recently, Jessie-May joined us from the UK in 2019, and Jordan came aboard last year.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251078\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251078\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web.jpg\" alt=\"bikerumor editorial team at eurobike\" width=\"1024\" height=\"829\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-297x240.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-800x648.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-120x97.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-768x622.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-696x563.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-519x420.jpg 519w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-297x240.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-800x648.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-120x97.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-768x622.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-696x563.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/bikerumor-team-eurobike-2019-web-519x420.jpg 519w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251078\">Tyler, Cory, Zach &amp; Jessie-May at Eurobike 2019.</figcaption></figure><p>I’m proud to say that we were one of the first major cycling sites to have a full-time female editor (<em>what’s up, Saris!</em>) and that I’ve always had an open door to anyone who could write and ride. A lot of awesome people have written for Bikerumor over the years, and I’m stoked that we’ve remained good friends even as they’ve moved on to other things.</p><h3>What’s next for Bikerumor?</h3><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group.jpg\" alt=\"allgear digital media group websites\" width=\"1883\" height=\"984\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1883px) 100vw, 1883px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group.jpg 1883w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group-297x155.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group-800x418.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/allgear-outdoor-digital-media-group-120x63.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfm