a-group-804x420.jpg 804w\"></a></p><p>Our team continues to grow, and that’s by design. I can’t honestly say I had a plan, and I certainly didn’t plan on selling Bikerumor last year, but I can say this: I built it to be bigger than me, so that our contributors could own their stories and their content, posting the types of stories they felt were most important or interesting. I built it to welcome all voices and riding styles.</p><p>And now, I get to welcome more new voices. We get to build it even bigger and better, with more resources to bring you more of the latest tech and cycling news you’ve come to expect from Bikerumor.</p><p>The sites in our AllGear portfolio are all amazing, and leaders in their categories. Personally, I’m excited to learn from all of them. We’ll likely share some of their best outdoor stories, and they’ll share ours.</p><p>Mostly, I’m just excited that we get to keep doing the things we’ve been doing, with the same team, and add fuel to that fire. I think you’re going to really enjoy what’s to come!</p><p>As always, thanks for reading,</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Tyler-Signature.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Tyler-Signature.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"38\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Tyler-Signature.jpg\"></a></p><p>Tyler Benedict<br>Founder &amp; Editor-in-Chief, Bikerumor</p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c2b859893ec21f6437270c7f60b50208787898f823ea381a178d7cea470ca71c","category":"Cycling"}